1
00:00:06,208 --> 00:00:06,808
(2006, the day
before Su Yunian starts work)

2
00:00:07,088 --> 00:00:08,208
Why not buy me a drink?

3
00:00:09,088 --> 00:00:09,648
You...

4
00:00:10,248 --> 00:00:11,607
You can drink?

5
00:00:12,008 --> 00:00:13,527
No. That's why I need to learn.

6
00:00:17,048 --> 00:00:18,167
Let's go.

7
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:19,727
Senior Chu.

8
00:00:23,088 --> 00:00:23,647
Go.

9
00:00:26,888 --> 00:00:27,687
Chief Zheng.

10
00:00:27,768 --> 00:00:28,968
We can't do this.

11
00:00:28,968 --> 00:00:30,207
This is a disregard for life.

12
00:00:33,928 --> 00:00:34,928
A disregard for life?

13
00:00:36,248 --> 00:00:38,647
What do you mean by that?

14
00:00:38,647 --> 00:00:40,568
Didn't you hear him
bring up Tu Jiasheng?

15
00:00:41,528 --> 00:00:43,488
You want us to end up
like Chief Phachai,

16
00:00:43,488 --> 00:00:44,447
thrown in prison,

17
00:00:44,447 --> 00:00:46,208
or even killed?

18
00:01:00,488 --> 00:01:01,488
It seems

19
00:01:03,488 --> 00:01:05,127
we'll have to sacrifice that guy.

20
00:01:06,928 --> 00:01:10,648
Handle it tonight.

21
00:01:12,927 --> 00:01:13,728
Okay?

22
00:01:21,888 --> 00:01:24,615
=The Glory Fades=

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,392
=Episode 4=
(Scapegoat)

24
00:01:36,728 --> 00:01:37,847
I don't understand.

25
00:01:38,728 --> 00:01:40,327
Why did you come to work here?

26
00:01:41,168 --> 00:01:41,968
Don't ask.

27
00:01:42,808 --> 00:01:43,927
You wouldn't understand it

28
00:01:44,528 --> 00:01:45,248
anyway.

29
00:01:52,968 --> 00:01:54,207
Let me make you a cocktail.

30
00:01:55,327 --> 00:01:56,847
It's called A Hint of Sorrow.

31
00:01:56,847 --> 00:01:57,567
How about that?

32
00:01:57,808 --> 00:01:58,968
A Hint of Sorrow?

33
00:01:59,767 --> 00:02:01,008
Such a poetic name.

34
00:02:03,728 --> 00:02:04,448
Hurry, Chu Bai.

35
00:02:04,448 --> 00:02:06,248
Prepare a Tangled Threads for Mr. Tu.

36
00:02:06,407 --> 00:02:07,248
Right away.

37
00:02:12,687 --> 00:02:15,007
Is that man Tu Jiasheng?

38
00:02:16,368 --> 00:02:16,968
Right.

39
00:02:17,127 --> 00:02:18,328
He's Tu Jiasheng.

40
00:02:20,727 --> 00:02:21,727
(These two drinks)

41
00:02:21,928 --> 00:02:24,567
(were crafted by Ruoxi
specially for him.)

42
00:02:24,928 --> 00:02:26,488
(I wonder if he still remembers.)

43
00:02:26,928 --> 00:02:28,528
(If he doesn't,)

44
00:02:29,127 --> 00:02:31,567
(it proves he never loved my sister.)

45
00:02:32,088 --> 00:02:33,048
(He even)

46
00:02:33,368 --> 00:02:34,687
(might be the murderer.)

47
00:02:35,768 --> 00:02:36,567
Server!

48
00:02:36,607 --> 00:02:37,768
Send the drink!

49
00:02:39,528 --> 00:02:40,607
I'll send it.

50
00:02:40,968 --> 00:02:41,607
You...

51
00:02:42,447 --> 00:02:43,447
You shouldn't go.

52
00:02:52,407 --> 00:02:54,048
Willows by the roadside sway.

53
00:02:54,607 --> 00:02:58,167
Tangled threads still can't compare
to a hint of sorrow.

54
00:02:59,048 --> 00:02:59,648
Mr. Tu.

55
00:03:00,167 --> 00:03:01,447
This is your Tangled Threads.

56
00:03:02,968 --> 00:03:04,127
(What about Tangled Threads?)

57
00:03:04,447 --> 00:03:05,607
Tangled Threads?

58
00:03:06,968 --> 00:03:08,007
A beautiful name.

59
00:03:08,368 --> 00:03:10,248
It reminds me of a Song dynasty poem.

60
00:03:11,687 --> 00:03:13,528
Willows by the roadside sway.

61
00:03:13,607 --> 00:03:18,208
Tangled threads still can't compare
to a hint of sorrow.

62
00:03:19,007 --> 00:03:20,167
So the other one

63
00:03:20,447 --> 00:03:21,928
shall be called A Hint of Sorrow.

64
00:03:24,808 --> 00:03:27,687
Is A Hint of Sorrow ordered by you?

65
00:03:28,727 --> 00:03:31,127
Bartender Chu recommended it.

66
00:03:32,407 --> 00:03:34,648
Mr. Tu, you don't mind

67
00:03:35,607 --> 00:03:36,808
I sit here, right?

68
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:39,088
How do you know these drinks' name

69
00:03:39,328 --> 00:03:41,607
come from that poem?

70
00:03:42,208 --> 00:03:45,184
(Changqingtai Mental Hospital)

71
00:03:52,007 --> 00:03:54,528
That's Jerith.

72
00:03:55,488 --> 00:03:56,887
He's mentally unstable.

73
00:03:58,088 --> 00:03:59,847
Tried to escape multiple times.

74
00:03:59,847 --> 00:04:01,088
Just got caught again.

75
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,488
With no family or friends.

76
00:04:03,887 --> 00:04:05,607
Nobody would care if he died.

77
00:04:09,567 --> 00:04:10,567
Chief Zheng.

78
00:04:10,887 --> 00:04:12,328
But this

79
00:04:12,607 --> 00:04:14,127
doesn't feel right.

80
00:04:17,488 --> 00:04:18,567
How about

81
00:04:19,328 --> 00:04:20,567
you take his place?

82
00:04:32,328 --> 00:04:33,128
Jerith.

83
00:04:33,688 --> 00:04:36,047
Jerith. Yes.

84
00:04:42,727 --> 00:04:43,688
Yes.

85
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:49,367
Let me go!

86
00:04:52,487 --> 00:04:54,607
It's finally done.

87
00:04:57,968 --> 00:04:59,688
I forgot to introduce myself.

88
00:05:00,128 --> 00:05:01,128
Hello, Mr. Tu.

89
00:05:01,208 --> 00:05:02,968
I'm Su Yunian, your new employee.

90
00:05:03,128 --> 00:05:04,167
I just finished training.

91
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:05,408
I start the day after tomorrow.

92
00:05:06,008 --> 00:05:07,968
You must think

93
00:05:08,528 --> 00:05:10,088
it's rude for a newcomer

94
00:05:10,088 --> 00:05:11,968
to sit with the boss

95
00:05:12,568 --> 00:05:14,008
like this, right?

96
00:05:16,407 --> 00:05:18,208
I'm afraid I have to be even ruder.

97
00:05:18,968 --> 00:05:19,648
Mr. Tu.

98
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,208
- Can I have a cigarette?
- Can I have a cigarette?

99
00:05:25,047 --> 00:05:26,727
(1998)
You're not the boss here, are you?

100
00:05:29,927 --> 00:05:31,008
Do I look like it?

101
00:05:32,727 --> 00:05:33,927
Not really.

102
00:05:35,328 --> 00:05:36,208
Why not?

103
00:05:36,287 --> 00:05:37,088
The vibe?

104
00:05:38,407 --> 00:05:39,888
You're too young.

105
00:05:40,568 --> 00:05:43,047
The boss here should be older.

106
00:05:43,807 --> 00:05:44,607
Also,

107
00:05:44,727 --> 00:05:45,768
I heard the boss

108
00:05:45,888 --> 00:05:47,648
is hard to meet.

109
00:05:49,847 --> 00:05:51,487
Now I'm really curious.

110
00:05:51,968 --> 00:05:54,367
What kind of person is the boss?

111
00:05:54,768 --> 00:05:55,727
Do you know him?

112
00:05:55,927 --> 00:05:56,968
Why is he so hard to meet?

113
00:05:59,528 --> 00:06:01,888
I heard from the recruiter

114
00:06:02,847 --> 00:06:04,768
that some people worked here for years

115
00:06:05,208 --> 00:06:07,727
without ever seeing the bosses.

116
00:06:08,807 --> 00:06:11,648
They say they're
several hidden billionaires.

117
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:13,448
Second-generation elites.

118
00:06:14,088 --> 00:06:15,367
Second-generation elites?

119
00:06:16,128 --> 00:06:17,287
Kids of officials or tycoons?

120
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,247
Both.

121
00:06:20,208 --> 00:06:21,208
Rumor has it

122
00:06:21,727 --> 00:06:23,688
they're three sworn brothers.

123
00:06:24,328 --> 00:06:25,807
The easiest to meet

124
00:06:26,088 --> 00:06:27,167
is Sixth Brother.

125
00:06:28,448 --> 00:06:29,648
He's straightforward,

126
00:06:30,047 --> 00:06:31,367
but hot-tempered

127
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:32,487
and ruthless.

128
00:06:32,727 --> 00:06:34,768
Don't make mistakes in front of him.

129
00:06:35,008 --> 00:06:36,487
He's absolutely strict.

130
00:06:38,247 --> 00:06:40,607
As for Fourth Brother and Fifth Brother,

131
00:06:40,888 --> 00:06:42,487
they're incredibly shrewd.

132
00:06:42,847 --> 00:06:44,128
We can't get near them.

133
00:06:44,128 --> 00:06:45,648
Seriously?

134
00:06:47,247 --> 00:06:48,727
Now you've got me curious.

135
00:06:49,247 --> 00:06:50,367
I must find a chance

136
00:06:50,367 --> 00:06:51,568
to get close to them.

137
00:06:52,847 --> 00:06:54,927
I hear they have powerful backing.

138
00:06:55,768 --> 00:06:57,807
This place looks
like an entertainment club,

139
00:06:58,328 --> 00:06:59,568
but in reality,

140
00:07:02,128 --> 00:07:04,208
it's an underground Personnel Bureau.

141
00:07:04,247 --> 00:07:05,847
Personnel Bureau?

142
00:07:06,407 --> 00:07:07,727
That's exaggerated.

143
00:07:08,568 --> 00:07:09,727
Stick with me.

144
00:07:09,847 --> 00:07:11,008
I've got the inside scoop.

145
00:07:14,648 --> 00:07:15,367
Okay.

146
00:07:15,487 --> 00:07:17,407
I'll follow your lead from now on.

147
00:07:29,287 --> 00:07:32,367
(Seems you still remember clearly)

148
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:33,968
(the first time you met my sister.)

149
00:07:35,287 --> 00:07:37,568
(Tu Jiasheng,
you've got some conscience.)

150
00:07:38,247 --> 00:07:40,047
(My sister didn't write those diaries)

151
00:07:40,287 --> 00:07:42,528
(line by line for nothing.)

152
00:07:56,688 --> 00:07:58,167
You just started smoking, didn't you?

153
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:01,247
If you're not addicted,

154
00:08:02,208 --> 00:08:03,167
better quit now.

155
00:08:06,088 --> 00:08:07,407
Mr. Tu, thanks for the cigarette

156
00:08:07,688 --> 00:08:09,088
and for your concern.

157
00:08:10,607 --> 00:08:12,768
The poem I mentioned earlier

158
00:08:12,768 --> 00:08:14,607
about these drinks

159
00:08:15,688 --> 00:08:18,008
seems to have stirred up your memories.

160
00:08:18,568 --> 00:08:19,247
Why?

161
00:08:19,247 --> 00:08:21,487
Do these two drinks

162
00:08:21,487 --> 00:08:23,128
have some special history here?

163
00:08:37,688 --> 00:08:39,208
Do you know An Ruoxi?

164
00:08:41,288 --> 00:08:42,408
An Ruoxi?

165
00:08:44,168 --> 00:08:45,487
I read about her in the news.

166
00:08:46,288 --> 00:08:48,487
The murdered woman a year ago, right?

167
00:08:48,647 --> 00:08:51,607
I heard she was once your woman.

168
00:08:51,887 --> 00:08:52,887
Some even say...

169
00:08:54,168 --> 00:08:54,968
What?

170
00:08:58,847 --> 00:08:59,448
Forget it.

171
00:08:59,688 --> 00:09:00,847
Let me toast you.

172
00:09:02,408 --> 00:09:03,208
Go on.

173
00:09:09,288 --> 00:09:10,408
They say

174
00:09:12,487 --> 00:09:13,887
that you killed her.

175
00:09:33,968 --> 00:09:35,607
Look at her face.

176
00:09:35,928 --> 00:09:37,847
Like a vixen reincarnated.

177
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:39,247
So annoying.

178
00:09:44,127 --> 00:09:45,808
Their vibes are different.

179
00:09:47,048 --> 00:09:48,647
Back then, An Ruoxi

180
00:09:49,168 --> 00:09:50,887
looked pure and innocent.

181
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:55,607
This girl looks sharp and calculating.

182
00:09:56,847 --> 00:09:58,088
Calculating?

183
00:09:59,007 --> 00:10:01,007
You have no idea what she's like.

184
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:03,208
She's brazen.

185
00:10:03,208 --> 00:10:04,208
Utterly brazen.

186
00:10:07,568 --> 00:10:08,727
You better be careful.

187
00:10:09,527 --> 00:10:10,928
With your mindset,

188
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,247
you're no match for her.

189
00:10:13,767 --> 00:10:16,607
I must say something.

190
00:10:17,288 --> 00:10:18,607
Yunyan has ranked first

191
00:10:18,607 --> 00:10:20,168
in performance for nearly a year.

192
00:10:20,367 --> 00:10:22,527
That takes brains, doesn't it?

193
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:28,408
Just wait.

194
00:10:28,527 --> 00:10:30,168
When she starts work,

195
00:10:30,328 --> 00:10:31,727
I'll make sure she suffers.

196
00:10:33,808 --> 00:10:36,408
Mr. Tu, may I ask one more question?

197
00:10:37,288 --> 00:10:39,168
If you think I shouldn't,

198
00:10:39,688 --> 00:10:41,288
you don't have to answer.

199
00:10:42,688 --> 00:10:43,487
Go ahead.

200
00:10:45,568 --> 00:10:48,007
The spokesperson on the news said

201
00:10:48,367 --> 00:10:49,568
An Ruoxi

202
00:10:49,568 --> 00:10:52,007
might have been killed
by a mentally ill person.

203
00:10:52,607 --> 00:10:55,367
Do you truly believe that?

204
00:10:57,408 --> 00:10:58,607
You shouldn't

205
00:10:59,688 --> 00:11:01,127
ask this.

206
00:11:01,847 --> 00:11:02,928
Unless

207
00:11:05,487 --> 00:11:07,808
you have some special connection
to An Ruoxi.

208
00:11:16,448 --> 00:11:17,448
So,

209
00:11:18,527 --> 00:11:20,288
do you have another identity

210
00:11:20,408 --> 00:11:22,007
you want to reveal to me?

211
00:11:25,007 --> 00:11:26,208
Sorry, Mr. Tu.

212
00:11:26,328 --> 00:11:27,928
I'm just a new employee.

213
00:11:28,328 --> 00:11:29,727
I still have a lot to learn

214
00:11:29,727 --> 00:11:30,847
about the job.

215
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:33,527
To become a better employee,

216
00:11:33,727 --> 00:11:35,767
I should go back and prepare.

217
00:11:35,847 --> 00:11:36,568
See you.

218
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:56,847
Ruoxi.

219
00:11:57,568 --> 00:11:58,448
Don't worry.

220
00:11:59,088 --> 00:12:00,247
Since I've come.

221
00:12:00,767 --> 00:12:02,288
I won't back down.

222
00:12:18,367 --> 00:12:19,288
Almost done.

223
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:20,247
Pull him up.

224
00:12:40,928 --> 00:12:41,727
Untie him.

225
00:12:57,168 --> 00:12:58,527
See if he's dead.

226
00:13:01,727 --> 00:13:03,767
Do I have to point a gun at you?

227
00:13:08,688 --> 00:13:09,487
He's dead for sure.

228
00:13:32,127 --> 00:13:33,367
Hello, it's me.

229
00:13:34,088 --> 00:13:36,527
I'm reporting that Jerith,
the suspect in the An Ruoxi case,

230
00:13:37,088 --> 00:13:39,448
attempted to escape
by jumping into the lake

231
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,968
and drowned.

232
00:13:42,487 --> 00:13:43,928
The body has been recovered.

233
00:13:44,568 --> 00:13:45,487
We can close the case.

234
00:14:03,392 --> 00:14:07,104
♪If the heart can't hear the sorrow♪

235
00:14:07,372 --> 00:14:10,639
♪It only makes everything look so fake♪

236
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:16,128
♪Your eyes resemble hers too much♪

237
00:14:16,601 --> 00:14:19,361
♪Who makes me forget whom♪

238
00:14:20,928 --> 00:14:24,581
♪The warmth in my heart is fading♪

239
00:14:24,832 --> 00:14:28,400
♪Every glance feels like atonement♪

240
00:14:29,792 --> 00:14:33,409
♪Ambiguity hidden in the night breeze♪

241
00:14:34,048 --> 00:14:39,072
♪Blows away the chance to explain♪

242
00:14:40,064 --> 00:14:43,544
♪I feel guilty♪

243
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:48,240
♪I'll have no regrets
even I leave quietly♪

244
00:14:49,408 --> 00:14:52,481
♪Even in tears♪

245
00:14:53,504 --> 00:14:57,218
♪It doesn't matter♪

246
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:01,176
♪We embrace in dreams♪

247
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:05,510
♪I let down all my defenses♪

248
00:15:06,816 --> 00:15:10,110
♪Though the story has its end♪

249
00:15:10,912 --> 00:15:19,200
♪I'll journey with you all my life♪
